    <stitle>STEERING COLUMN ASSEMBLY, TILT/TELESCOPING - INSTALL</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>INSTALL</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="0">
            <title>STEERING COLUMN</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the four (4) bolts, washers and nuts that attach the steering column bracket to
                    the dash panel. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s05009t_14.xml" xrefid="hl0500901">TORQUE CHART
                        <xref refid="hl0500901"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    for the recommended torque.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the horn wire at the connector.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the trailer brake control on the steering column.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the steering wheel on the column. Refer to the
                    <hotlnk document="s05009t_14.xml" xrefid="hl0500901">TORQUE CHART
                        <xref refid="hl0500901"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    for the recommended torque.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align the slip shaft with the yoke by referring to the marks made at removal. Use a new
                    shear-type pinch bolt in the yoke. Refer to the
                    <hotlnk document="s05009t_14.xml" xrefid="hl0500901">TORQUE CHART
                        <xref refid="hl0500901"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    for the proper torquing procedure.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
